    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Religious or worldy communities of knights bound by rules of chivalry, with the main purpose of an ideal or charitable task. Originally these societies had a military and spiritual nature and members were elevated to nobility. Since the 18th century they became institutions for rewarding and acknowledging services to society.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
